               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Bustan by Saʻdī
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_252-item1">
                     <author key="person_100206721" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/100206721/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Saʻdī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">سعدی <addName xml:lang="ar" type="nisbah">شيرازی</addName>
                        </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_328">Bustan.</title>
                     <note>F1a, notes of acquisition(?) dated 1208? (1793-4?) and 1228 (1813. Final folio, verso: a) Ex libris C J Doyle A.D. 1820. b) Impression of small rectangular seal, not read. The MS ends with a long 'colophon' in verse, describing how it was made at the command of the Nawwab Intizam al-Mulk Amir al-Daulah Nusrat Jang, whose name was Haidar and that the gilding was carried out between 1 Rajab and the 'Id (at the end of Ramadan, presumably) in the year 1202 (7 April - 6 July 1788). Ruled margins. Headings in red. Each hemistich of the text has gilding around it. The initial opening has elaborate illumination.</note>
                     <incipit>Bi-nam-i Khudawand-i jan-afarin</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>As for Codrington/Reade No 251.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Add ref. to Donations Register.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
